# Configuration Guide â€“ Face Recognition Web Service

This guide explains how to configure and launch the face recognition web service using command-line parameters. No configuration file is requiredâ€”setup is performed directly via the console or by registering the executable as a Windows service.

---

## Prerequisites

Before configuring or launching the service, ensure the following requirements are met:

### System Requirements
- **Operating System**: Windows 10/11 or Windows Server 2016+
- **Architecture**: x64 (64-bit)
- **Permissions**: Administrator rights (required to bind ports and register services)

### Dependencies
- [Windows Runtime](https://www.microsoft.com/es-es/download/details.aspx?id=39717)
- [Microsoft SQL Server 2017+](https://www.microsoft.com/es-es/evalcenter/download-sql-server-2017-rtm)
- [ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/connect/odbc/download-odbc-driver-for-sql-server?view=sql-server-ver17)

---

## Available Configuration Parameters

Omitting any of the parameters listed below will apply the default value.

### ðŸ”¹ Set Domain

Use the `--domain=` parameter to specify an IPv4 domain.

- **Default**: `127.0.0.1` (localhost)

### ðŸ”¹ Set Port

Use the `--port=` parameter to specify the listening port.

- **Note**: Ensure the selected port is open and not blocked by firewall rules.
- **Default**: `80`

### ðŸ”¹ Connect to the Database

Use the `--db.uri=` parameter to define the connection string using the Microsoft ODBC Driver.

- Refer to the [ODBC Driver 17 connection string guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/integration-services/import-export-data/connect-to-an-odbc-data-source-sql-server-import-and-export-wizard?view=sql-server-ver17) for advanced options.

**Example for testing environments:**
```bash
--db.uri="Driver={ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server};Server=localhost,1433;Database=BiometricDB;Uid=sa;Pwd=YourPassword;"
- Default: None (this parameter is required)
  
### ðŸ”¹ Set Log Directory
Use the --log.dir= parameter to specify where system logs will be stored.
- Default: C:\ProgramData\BiometricWebService\Bio_v10.1.1_logDirectory

## Example command

    face-recognition-api.exe ^
  --domain=10.85.37.92 ^
  --port=8888 ^
  --db.uri="Driver={ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server};Server=localhost,1433;Database=BiometricDB;Uid=sa;Pwd=YourPassword;" ^
  --log.dir="C:\ProgramData\BiometricWebService\Bio_v10.1.1_logDirectory"

  

